<p>My <a href="https://www.rousette.org.uk/archives/zsa-voyager/">ZSA Voyager</a> keyboard has a new travelling companion: a <a href="https://www.zsa.io/voyager/navigator">ZSA Navigator</a>. I love using it, but it has taken a bit of time to figure out the best configuration for me.</p>
<figure role="group"><img
 srcset="https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/bianca_and_voyager.jpeg?&w=100 100w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/bianca_and_voyager.jpeg?&w=200 200w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/bianca_and_voyager.jpeg?&w=400 400w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/bianca_and_voyager.jpeg?&w=800 800w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/bianca_and_voyager.jpeg?&w=1000 1000w,https://www.rousette.org.uk/.netlify/images?url=https://f000.backblazeb2.com/file/bsag-blog-imgs/bianca_and_voyager.jpeg?&w=1500 1500w"
